topic = "Compilation"
help_text = "Pressing one of these buttons will compile the respective stage. If you want to compile multiple stages and maybe even run the game when compilation has finished, use the [i]Batching[/i] section instead.

[i]BSP[/i] (Binary Space Partitioning) compiles the physical structure of your map. This is sufficient to play your map, but there will be no optimization or shadows.

[i]VIS[/i] (visibility) is for performance optimization. Compiles visibility (which parts of your map can be seen from which position - things that can't be  seen aren't rendered) and automatically generates ambient sounds. Only works if your map doesn't have a leak.

[i]LIGHT[/i] compiles lights and shadows.

[i]Pause[/i] prevents the compiler window from closing automatically after compilation has finished so you can read the compile log."

